sentences: In 1880 he was admitted to the Théâtre Lyrique orchestra, where he began studying composition and instrumentation, but also law, in order to please his parents.
Although since he was small he showed great liking and aptitudes for the music, he had to follow, by paternal decision, a Law career, which he finished in Madrid in 1885.
In 1895 he was a director at the Spanish Teatro Real.
In 1896, he was the director of the Concert Academy of the Royal Theater.
After 1898 he was the director of Orfeon Ecos de Madrid.
In the 1900s almost was a broker of Bolsa de Madrid.

His works in the Royal Theatre of Spain are many: Hansel and Gretel, El oro del Rin, Loreley (1916), Luisa (1919), Mona Lisa (1923), Yolanda (1923), Jardín de oriente, La novia vendida (1924), La virgen de mayo (1925).
